Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Trim the @courgette{1} then quarter lengthways. Chop widthways into small pieces. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125%g}. Halve the @lemon{½}. Peel the @garlic clove{1} and pop into foil with a drizzle of @oil{} and scrunch to enclose it. Roast on a #baking tray{} in your oven until soft, ~{10-12%mins}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #medium frying pan{} on medium high heat (preferably a #non stick pan{}). Once hot, add the chopped courgette and cook, turning occasionally, until golden brown and softened, ~{4-5%mins}. Add half the tomatoes and cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes} more. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Pour the @scrambled egg mix{1} into a #bowl{} or a #jug{}, season with salt and pepper and beat with a #whisk{} or a #fork{}. Add the @dried Italian herbs{½} and half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g} and mix.

Pour in the egg mixture, lower the heat to medium and cover with a #lid{} or #tin foil{}. Allow to cook for ~{15-20%mins} until the frittata is set all the way through.

> Check occasionally and if the sides of the pan are starting to colour too quickly turn the heat down a bit.

Remove the garlic from the foil, leave to cool slightly and mash with the back of a fork. Finely chop half of the @wild rocket{40%g} and pop into a medium bowl. Finely snip the @chives{1} using #scissors{} into the bowl with the rocket. Add the roasted garlic, @olive oil{for the dressing}, the remaining cheese, a squeeze of lemon juice and season with salt and pepper. Mix well and add a little more olive oil or lemon if you need to, it should have a pourable consistency.

Halve the @ciabatta{1} (as if you were making a sandwich). Pop onto a baking tray and drizzle with @olive oil{}. Bake until warmed through and lightly toasted, ~{3-4%mins}. Meanwhile, pop the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and @olive oil{2%tbsp} into a medium bowl and season with salt and pepper. Add the remaining tomatoes and rocket but don't mix together until you are ready to serve!

Once the frittata has cooked through, cut into slices and share between your plates.

> You can carefully flip it onto a chopping board or large plate first if you want to.

Toss the salad together with its dressing and serve alongside the frittata with the toasted ciabatta. Drizzle the pesto over the frittata and enjoy!